---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { ArrowLeft, ExternalLink, Rss } from 'lucide-astro';
---

<Layout title="About - The Rhyne Report" description="Learn more about The Rhyne Report and its author">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <header class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About</h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-600 font-light">
          The story behind The Rhyne Report
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="mb-8">
          <img 
            src="/placeholder-author.jpg" 
            alt="Author profile"
            class="w-32 h-32 rounded-full mx-auto object-cover mb-6"
            style="display: none;"
          />
        </div>

        <h2>Welcome</h2>
        
        <p>
          The Rhyne Report is a personal blog focused on sharing insights, thoughts, and observations 
          on technology, business, and life. This platform serves as a space for deeper exploration 
          of topics that matter, from technical deep-dives to broader industry analysis.
        </p>

        <h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
        
        <p>
          This blog covers a diverse range of topics, including:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Technology & Development:</strong> Insights into software development, emerging technologies, and technical best practices</li>
          <li><strong>Industry Analysis:</strong> Observations on market trends, business strategy, and industry developments</li>
          <li><strong>Personal Reflections:</strong> Thoughts on productivity, learning, and professional growth</li>
          <li><strong>Reviews & Recommendations:</strong> Books, tools, and resources worth sharing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Philosophy</h2>
        
        <p>
          The goal of The Rhyne Report is to provide thoughtful, well-researched content that offers 
          genuine value to readers. Every post is crafted with care, focusing on quality over quantity 
          and depth over surface-level commentary.
        </p>

        <p>
          The site itself embodies these principles through its clean, minimal design that prioritizes 
          readability and fast loading times. Built with modern web technologies like Astro and 
          Tailwind CSS, it represents a commitment to both excellent user experience and technical excellence.
        </p>

        <h2>Connect</h2>
        
        <p>
          I welcome thoughtful discussion and feedback. While comments aren't enabled on the blog posts 
          themselves, you can reach out through social media or email to continue the conversation.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
          <a 
            href="https://x.com/jdrhyne" 
            target="_blank" 
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl transition-colors font-medium shadow-elegant hover:shadow-elegant-lg"
          >
            <ExternalLink class="w-4 h-4" />
            Follow on X
          </a>
          <a 
            href="/rss.xml"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl transition-colors font-medium shadow-elegant hover:shadow-elegant-lg"
          >
            <Rss class="w-4 h-4" />
            RSS Feed
          </a>
        </div>

        <h2>Technical Details</h2>
        
        <p>
          For those interested in the technical implementation, this site is built with:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Astro:</strong> Static site generator for optimal performance</li>
          <li><strong>Tailwind CSS:</strong> Utility-first CSS framework for rapid styling</li>
          <li><strong>TypeScript:</strong> Type-safe development experience</li>
          <li><strong>Markdown:</strong> Content authoring with frontmatter metadata</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          The source code is available on GitHub for those interested in how everything works 
          behind the scenes or who want to use it as a starting point for their own blog.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t-2 border-gray-100 text-center">
        <a 
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-gray-700 hover:text-blue-700 transition-colors font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-50"
        >
          <ArrowLeft class="w-5 h-5" />
          Back to Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>